\pard\f0\fs28 Submerged, perennial aquatic herbs, with creeping rhizomes. Leaves alternate or subopposite, linear, sheathing at the base. Flowers unisexual, small, solitary or in falcate cymes. Male flowers pedunculate; perianth absent or cupular; stamens 1-3; anthers connate, sessile, opening by longitudinal slits. Female flowers sessile or shortly pedunculate; perianth absent or cupular or of 3 segments; carpels 1-9, free, with 1 ovule; styles simple or divided into 2 filiform stigmas. Fruitlets achene- or nut-like; seeds without endosperm.
